# UI consistency (GymBroPortal)

Complements `angular-frontend.mdc`, `figma-design-system.mdc`, and `design-system-enforcer.mdc`. Prefer **global and shared** fixes over feature one-offs.

## Enforce

- **Spacing system** — section stacks `gap-6`; within cards/sections `gap-4`; card body padding `p-5` where not already defined by `app-ui-panel-card` or the shell. Responsive: stack on small viewports, no horizontal overflow (`min-w-0`, scroll wrappers for tables).
- **Button hierarchy** — one clear **primary** action per view (solid); secondary/outline for alternatives; destructive only where semantics require it. Route all actions through **`app-button`**.
- **Aligned cards and sections** — same max-width, gutters, and header rhythm as sibling pages; use **`app-page-header`** and shared panel/card wrappers.

## Handle null / empty

- **Missing text or optional fields:** show **“Not set”** (or hide the row/block if hiding is clearer and matches existing screens). Use the same phrasing app-wide.
- **Images / media:** placeholder or empty state consistent with existing preview components—not ad-hoc icons per page.

## Improve

- **Visual hierarchy** — title → description → primary content → secondary actions; reduce competing bold blocks and mismatched font sizes.
- **Spacing rhythm** — consistent vertical rhythm between sections; avoid arbitrary `gap-3` / `gap-5` unless part of a defined exception.

## Forbid

- **Raw placeholders** — no `-`, `undefined`, `null`, or empty strings shown to users as content.
- **Inconsistent empty copy** — mix of “N/A”, “—”, and “Not set” on the same class of field; pick **“Not set”** (or hide) per above.
